The electrografting of IPA was achieved in 7 scans (
                           Fig. S2
                        ) and the reduction peaks did not disappear. This was attributed to thin film that forms due to blocking of position 3 and 5 for multilayer formation. The Au-IPA electrode still reduces 5-DIPA due to long range electron transfer, hence the stable reduction peak even at IPA modified surface. The immobilization of AmGQDs and CoTCPhOPc onto the gold electrode was followed as shown in Scheme 1. The presence of amine group on the edge of the amine functionalized AmGQD acted as site for binding on the di-basic carboxylic acid [16] of Au-IPA after activating with EDC and NHS (carbodiimide amide coupling). The amine functional groups of AmGQDs were used to immobilize CoTCPhOPc using carbodiimide chemistry. The CoTCPhOPc carboxylic acid functional groups were activated using EDC and NHS and reacted with amine functionalized groups of AmGQDs to form amide bonds.
